From: Armbian
Subject: orangepi-zero-plus2-h3: DRAM 408 + ZQ/ODT (stability)

The board is now mainlined in u-boot, but upstream orangepi_zero_plus2_h3_defconfig
runs DRAM at 672 with ODT off. Armbian's previous board defconfig tuned this board
to DRAM_CLK=408 + DRAM_ZQ + DRAM_ODT_EN for stability (same family-wide H3/H2+ DRAM
issue as orangepi-zero / orangepi-r1). Re-apply that tuning on top of the upstream
defconfig (the old add-the-whole-defconfig patch was dropped now that the board +
DT are upstream).

--- a/configs/orangepi_zero_plus2_h3_defconfig
+++ b/configs/orangepi_zero_plus2_h3_defconfig
@@ -1,10 +1,11 @@
 CONFIG_ARM=y
 CONFIG_ARCH_SUNXI=y
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="sun8i-h3-orangepi-zero-plus2"
-CONFIG_DRAM_CLK=672
+CONFIG_DRAM_CLK=408
+CONFIG_DRAM_ZQ=3881979
 CONFIG_SPL=y
 CONFIG_MACH_SUN8I_H3=y
-# CONFIG_DRAM_ODT_EN is not set
+CONFIG_DRAM_ODT_EN=y
 CONFIG_MMC_SUNXI_SLOT_EXTRA=2
 CONFIG_SPL_SUNXI_LED_STATUS=y
 CONFIG_SPL_SUNXI_LED_STATUS_GPIO=362
